The paper deals with distributed machine learning, which is a subfield of both machine learning and distributed computing. The focus is on data-dependent dispatching, which involves partitioning the data in a way that satisfies important conditions for accurate distributed learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with classification rules and real-world image and advertising datasets, which suggests that it may also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
